Template: vaulthalla/init-db
Type: boolean
Default: false
Description: Initialize a PostgreSQL database for Vaulthalla?
 Vaulthalla requires a PostgreSQL database. If enabled, the installer will
 attempt to create a local database and user using the local PostgreSQL
 server.
 .
 If disabled, create the required database and user manually (local or remote)
 before first runtime setup.
 See /usr/share/doc/vaulthalla/README.Debian for instructions.

Template: vaulthalla/superadmin-uid
Type: string
Default:
Description: Linux UID to assign as super-admin (blank to skip pre-seeding)
 The super-admin account is mapped to a Linux user for privileged operations.
 Enter a numeric UID, or 'auto' to detect from the current interactive session.
 Leave blank to skip install-time UID assignment.

Template: vaulthalla/configure-nginx
Type: boolean
Default: false
Description: Configure nginx reverse proxy for Vaulthalla web (safe mode)?
 If enabled, the installer will try to enable a conservative nginx site config
 for Vaulthalla only when the host appears safe for automatic changes.
 .
 The installer will skip configuration when nginx is missing, inactive, already
 serving non-nginx listeners on ports 80/443, or running custom site layouts.
 .
 If disabled or skipped, configure your reverse proxy manually.
